Business Brief -- Morgan Stanley  Co.:
   Coltec Plans Debt Offerings
   As Part of Recapitalization
Coltec said in a filing with the Securities and Exchange
Commission that it will offer $200 million in senior notes
due 2000 and $250 million in senior subordinated notes due
2002. Coltec last month said it plans a $577.5 million
initial public offering as part of the plan to reduce its
debt.
   The company, formerly Colt Industries Inc., was acquired
by the Morgan Stanley  Co. unit of Morgan Stanley Group and
affiliates in 1988 for $660 million.